    <task>
      <statement><p>Use the data in Example<nbsp/>10 to find the rate of change in Oregon cancer diagnoses between 2007 and 2017.</p>
<p><fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>363.5\ {\textstyle\frac{\rm\mathstrut diagnoses}{\rm\mathstrut yr}}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <solution><p>To find the rate of change between 2007 and 2017, calculate</p>
<p><me>\frac{23052 - 19417}{2017 - 2007} = 363.5
              \text{.}</me></p>
<p>So the rate of change was <m>{363.5\ {\textstyle\frac{\rm\mathstrut diagnoses}{\rm\mathstrut yr}}}\text{.}</m></p>
</solution>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement><p>And what was the rate of change between 2018 and 2012?</p>
